-- Global Sugar Exports Seen Advancing 1.6% to 53 Mln Tons by UN
-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-11-08T11:36:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-08/global-sugar-exports-seen-advancing-1-6-to-53-mln-tons-by-un.html
Global trade will rebound on
increased exports from Brazil, the world’s largest producer, the
 United Nations ’ Food & Agriculture Organization said in a
report.
* Brazil to supply 44% of world sugar trade in 2012-13 season
* India’s sugar exports will decline to 2.3m t from 3m t in
2011-12
* Russia’s sugar imports will rise to 1.2m t from 1m t in
2011-12
NOTE: The 2012-13 season started last month  To contact the reporter on this story:
